values.name: Conversation
values.doc: A project to build natural language into apps, bots, and IoT devices.

values.name: Orchestration
values.doc: A project to connect and orchestrate Conversation, Custom question answering and LUIS projects together in one single project.

values.name: CustomConversationSummarization
values.doc: A project to build conversation summarization models which are able to summarize long conversations.

values.name: Conversation
values.doc: Specifies the format for a conversational project.

values.name: Luis
values.doc: Specifies the format for an application that was exported from LUIS.

values.name: Utf16CodeUnit
values.doc: The offset and length values will correspond to UTF-16 code units. Use this option if your application is written in a language that support Unicode, for example Java, JavaScript.

values.name: returnLongestOverlap
values.doc: When two or more components are found in the text and overlap, the component with the longest set of characters is returned.

values.name: requireExactOverlap
values.doc: All components must overlap at the exact same characters in the text for the entity to return. If one of the defined components is not matched or predicted, the entity will not return.

values.name: separateComponents
values.doc: Every component's match or prediction is returned as a separate instance of the entity.

values.name: combineComponents
values.doc: When two or more components are found in the text and overlap, the components' spans are merged together into one span combining all of them.

values.name: advanced
values.doc: Trains using fine-tuned neural network transformer models. Can train multilingual projects.

values.name: standard
values.doc: Faster training times for quicker iterations.

values.name: percentage
values.doc: Split the data into training and test sets according to user-defined percentages.

values.name: manual
values.doc: Split the data according to the chosen dataset for every example in the data.
